title: Frame By Frame - Cassadee Pope - 2013
description:
Frame by Frame is the debut solo studio album of American singer-songwriter Cassadee Pope. Originally, Pope was the lead vocalist for the American rock band Hey Monday, whom of which decided to begin a hiatus in 2011. While each member pursued in their own side projects, Pope decided to go solo and auditioned for the third season of the popular singing competition The Voice in 2012.

After turning the chairs of all four judges in the Blind Audition round, she chose country singer Blake Shelton to be her mentor. Pope advanced through to all ten rounds of the competition and eventually won the title of winner of The Voice 2012, while also achieving a high number of downloads of covers of songs she sang on the show that regularly topped the iTunes sales charts along the way.
